citeinfo.title: Backcountry Units in Denali National Park and Preserve

pubinfo.publish: National Park Service, Alaska Regional Office

descript.abstract: Backcountry use units for Denali National Park and Preserve. Designated wilderness within the park is divided into a number of units for the purpose of managing use levels and wilderness character. Each unit has a pre-set limit on the number of overnight campers permitted within the unit.
descript.purpose: Provide appropriate scale data to meet park management needs.
descript.supplinf:
Unit boundaries were digitized from USGS 1:63360 scale DLG (hydrology) and DEM (5000' contours) data as well as USGS topographical quadrangles. Where unit boundaries followed water courses the corresponding DLG water course was used. Where the boundary follows the 5000' contour the corresponding arcs derived from 1:63360 USGS DEM data were used. Other boundaries were digitized from 1:63360 scale USGS topographical quadrangles. Attribute field called 'aunit' identifies each backcountry unit.
Coverage was updated in February 2003 to reflect the addition of units covering the portion of the park that had not been delineated before.
